    IDS_CTRLHELP            "{\\bnsi\\bnsicpg1252\\deff0\\deflang4105{\\fonttbl{\\f0\\fnil\\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}{\\f1\\fswiss\\fcharset0 Arial;}}\n{\\*\\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1503;}\\viewkind4\\uc1\\pard\\ul\\b\\f0\\fs20 How to lookup Help for Controls and Dialog boxes.\\ulnone\\b0\\par\n\\par\nTo activate the help for control and dialog boxes, right click on the control or dialog box that you wish to look up help information on. Next click on\\b  ""Intelligent Help"" \\b0 at the bottom.\\par\n\\par\nNext the intelligent help dialog box will appear. Select on the left side property or function you wish to lookup. On the right, the help information will be shown to you. All information on the selection will appear there and will even show you the correctly formatted AutoLisp syntax at the bottom for that control or dialog box.\\par\n\\par\nFor ease of use, at the bottom you will notice one or two buttons titled; ""Copy to Clipboard"". Click one of those buttons and you will be able then simply paste the code into your AutoLisp file.\\f1\\par\n}\n "
    ID_FILE_REGISTERCONTROLS "Register/Unregister controls"
END

